From ed1292344bba1d5ca96b81c82c9556c071a981ad Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mykola Hlukhenkyi <m.hlukhenkyi@inango-systems.com>
Date: Tue, 2 Sep 2025 23:20:40 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] miniupnpd: GetGenericPortMappingEntry error codes

miniupnpd does not process all redirect rules from the system bus,
but only collects information for rules with Origin=UPnP.
So when the user requests index for rule that is not Origin=UPnP,
miniupnpd gets nothing from bus and returns
"SpecifiedArrayIndexInvalid" error

Solution:
* Modify `get_redirect_rule_by_index_pm` to pass the `is_upnp_rule`
 variable so that users can determine the received rules were created
 by UPnP

References: PCF-2043

Signed-off-by: Mykola Hlukhenkyi <m.hlukhenkyi@inango-systems.com>
---
